Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: SquareLoop's Mobile Alert Network is the only LBS application currently available that enables users to opt-in to receive information based on their current or past location. The Mobile Alert Network platform can be used for critical communications, such as emergency, weather and traffic alerts, and advertiser supported content. Another unique feature of the Mobile Alert Network is that it does not require tracking a user's location in real time. Instead, SquareLoop's patented technology - which was originally developed by The MITRE Corp. for military applications - puts the intelligence in the handset in order to maintain individual privacy. In another sign of increasing noise in the global positioning and wireless location-based service markets, yet another startup has emerged: Reston, Virginia-based SquareLoop. A number of SquareLoopâ€™s specific features center around user privacy, giving them the ability to opt-in or out of services. The company also won an Emerging Technology award earlier this year from the Cellular Telecommunications Industry Association (CTIA).
Industry Groups: Apps, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Mobile, Navigation and Mapping, Platforms, Software

Description: Desktoptwo develops internet based operating systems and free online storage systems for businesses.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Desktoptwo is another contender in the market of internet based "operating systems". Developed by parent company, Sapotek, Desktoptwo remains in beta as of December 2007. It claims to have acquired more than 160,000 active users since its launch in August 2006.  Desktoptwo is fully web-based and requires Flash player to operate. A key, and possibly winning, feature is the hard drive application. Users are given 1 GB of free storage on Desktoptwo. While a slew of companies offer free online storage (see [here](http://www.techcrunch.com/2006/01/31/the-online-storage-gang/)), users may prefer Desktoptwo as it is integrated with many other features.  Some (self-explanatory) applications found on Desktoptwo include: Mail -- with POP3 functionality, Address book, My Website Creator, mp3 player, and RSS Reader. Also, Desktoptwo uses a number of open-source applications, notably Open Office as its productivity suite.  Unlike some other online desktops, the web applications found on Desktoptwo are built on the same open source scripting language as Desktoptwo itself -- PHP. Sapotek has also created a Spanish language version of Desktoptwo called Computadora.de Competitors include [YouOS](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/youOS), [eyeOS](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/eyeos), and [G.ho.st](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/G.ho.st).
